      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;optimization-context&#34;&gt;Optimization context&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s imagine for a moment we are trying to solve a class of &lt;em&gt;constrained&lt;/em&gt; optimization problems of the form&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;$$\begin{align*}&#xD;&#xA;    &amp;\inf_x f(x) \\&#xD;&#xA;    &amp;\text{subject to } &amp;g_i(x) \leq 0 \text{ for } 1 \leq i \leq m \\&#xD;&#xA;                        &amp;&amp;h_j(x) = 0, \text{ for } 1 \leq j \leq n&#xD;&#xA;\end{align*} &#xD;&#xA;$$&lt;p&gt;&#xA;where $f, g_1, \ldots, g_m, h_1, \ldots, h_n \in \mathcal{C}$ for $\mathcal{C}$ a fixed class of smooth functions. We fix such a problem $(P)$. How should we do it?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
